Label: CPT-1
Comment: CPT1 (mitochondrial isoform) aka carnitine palmitoyl transferase

Label: UCP2
Comment: Mitochondrial transporter proteins which creates proton leaks across the inner mitochondrial membrane, allowing uncoupling oxidative phosphorylation from ATP synthesis. As a result, energy is dissipated in the form of heat. Source [https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P55851]
